HEADWORD: Gymnogen
<hw>Gym"no*gen</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧m"n⟦osl⟧*j⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>gymno`s</grk> naked + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of a class of plants, so called by
<persfn>Lindley</persfn>, because the ovules are fertilized by direct
contact of the pollen. Same as <er>Gymnosperm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gymnoglossa</ent>⟦br⟧
